```sql
PRAGMA foreign_keys=OFF;  -- Must be first, before any table manipulation
CREATE TABLE `__new_tasks` ( ... session_id text, ... );
INSERT INTO `__new_tasks`(...) SELECT ... FROM `tasks`;
DROP TABLE `tasks`;
ALTER TABLE `__new_tasks` RENAME TO `tasks`;
PRAGMA foreign_keys=ON;  -- Re-enable after migration completes
```

CAVEAT: None - this is the standard pattern for SQLite table rebuilds when foreign key constraints exist. The PRAGMA must precede all schema-altering statements in the migration file itself; client-side settings are irrelevant once the migration file begins executing.

